column1: Table S1: DESeq2 differential gene expression analysis of Staphylococcus aureus USA300 wild type after AGXX® treatment in three biological replicates. S. aureus wild type cells were grown in 3 biological replicates and harvested before and after 30 min exposure to 4.5 µg/ml AGXX®. The RNA-isolation, library preparation, sequencing and mapping was performed as described in the methods section. Transcripts were analyzed for differential  gene expression using the software DEseq2 included in the ReadXplorer v2.2 software. The signal intensity value (A-value) was calculated by log2 base mean of normalized read counts and the signal intensity ratio (M-value) by log2-fold change. The evaluation of the differential RNAseq data was performed using an adjusted p-value cut-off of P ≤ 0.05 and a signal intensity ratio (M-value) cut-off of ≥ 0.6 or ≤ - 0.6 (printed in bold). Genes were classified into regulons according to the RegPrecise database and those published previously (Mäder et al., 2016).
